Then from the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABP,$
\[BP^2 = 3^2 + x^2 - 2 \cdot 3 \cdot x \cdot \cos \angle APB,\]and from the Law of Cosines on triangle $CDP,$
\[DP^2 = 8^2 + x^2 - 2 \cdot 8 \cdot x \cdot \cos \angle CPD.\]Since $\angle APB = 180^\circ - \angle CPD,$
\begin{align*}
\frac{BP^2}{DP^2} &= \frac{3^2 + x^2 - 2 \cdot 3 \cdot x \cdot \cos \angle APB}{8^2 + x^2 - 2 \cdot 8 \cdot x \cdot \cos \angle CPD} \\
&= \frac{3^2 + x^2 - 2 \cdot 3 \cdot x \cdot \cos (180^\circ - \angle CPD)}{8^2 + x^2 - 2 \cdot 8 \cdot x \cdot \cos \angle CPD} \\
&= \frac{3^2 + x^2 + 2 \cdot 3 \cdot x \cdot \cos \angle CPD}{8^2 + x^2 - 2 \cdot 8 \cdot x \cdot \cos \angle CPD}.
\end{align*}By the Law of Cosines on triangle $PCD,$
\[\cos \angle CPD = \frac{8^2 + x^2 - 13^2}{2 \cdot 8 \cdot x} = \frac{x^2 - 105}{16x}.\]Then
